4772","snippet":"The likes of England, France, and Spain will have their eyes on the famous FIFA trophy, while hosts USA will bid to deliver their best ever performance in the tournament's modern format.","publishedDate":1781694998000,"id":"5","domain":"sportingnews.com","maxVerbatimWordLimit":30,"publicDomain":true},{"title":"All 48 Teams, Draw Results &amp; Predictions","url":"https://worldcupwiki.com/groups/","snippet":"The 2026 FIFA World Cup is the biggest in history. For the first time 48 teams compete across 12 groups. The United States, Canada and Mexico share hosting duties.","publishedDate":1775979775000,"id":"6","domain":"worldcupwiki.com","maxVerbatimWordLimit":30,"publicDomain":true},{"title":"12 Groups, 48 Teams, 1 Champion — Full Guide","url":"https://www.fifaworldcupnews.com/fifa-world-cup-2026-brackets/","snippet":"With 48 nations competing across three host countries (the United States, Canada, and Mexico), 16 stadiums, and a staggering 104 matches, this is a World Cup like no other.","publishedDate":1783042596000,"id":"7","domain":"fifaworldcupnews.com","maxVerbatimWordLimit":30,"publicDomain":true},{"title":"What’s the full match schedule, groups and format for World Cup 2026?","url":"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/5/7/whats-the-full-match-schedule-groups-and-format-for-world-cup-2026","snippet":"Argentina will look to defend the trophy they lifted under their iconic captain, Lionel Messi, at Qatar 2022, while Cape Verde, Curacao, Jordan, and Uzbekistan will make their debut at the finals.","publishedDate":1778763771000,"id":"8","domain":"aljazeera.com","maxVerbatimWordLimit":30,"publicDomain":true},{"title":"2026 FIFA World Cup","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2026_FIFA_World_Cup","snippet":"Starting with the 2026 edition, the FIFA World Cup expanded to 48 teams, an increase of 16 teams compared to the previous seven tournaments.[14] As approved by the FIFA Council on March 14, 2023, the teams were split into 12 groups of 4 teams, with the top 2 teams in each group and the 8 best third-place teams progressing to a new round of 32.[15] It is the first expansion and format change since 1998.[16]\nThe total number of matches played increased from 64 to 104, and the number of matches played by teams reaching the semifinals increased from 7 to 8. The tournament lasts 39 days, an increase from the 32 days of the 2014 and 2018 tournaments.[17][18] Each team still plays three group matches.[19][20] The final matchday at club level for players named in the final squads was May 24, 2026; clubs had to release their players by May 25, with exceptions granted to players participating in continental club competition finals up until May 30. The 56 days of the combined rest, release, and tournament periods remain identical to the 2010, 2014, and 2018 tournaments.[15]\n\nOther expansion formats explored\nThe expansion to 48 teams had already been approved on January 10, 2017, when it was initially decided that the tournament would include 16 groups of 3 teams, and 80 matches in total, with the top two teams of each group progressing to a round of 32.[","publishedDate":1783127608000,"id":"9","domain":"wikipedia.org","maxVerbatimWordLimit":-1,"publicDomain":false},{"title":"World Cup 2026: Full match schedule, groups, teams and start times","url":"https://www.aljazeera.com/sports/2026/6/11/world-cup-2026-full-match-schedule-groups-teams-and-start-times","snippet":"� Group A: Mexico, South Africa, Korea Republic (South Korea), Czechia (Czech Republic)","publishedDate":1781159857000,"id":"10","domain":"aljazeera.com","maxVerbatimWordLimit":30,"publicDomain":true}]}</div><button class="mantine-focus-auto _copyButton_q7lj1_717 m_87cf2631 acme-UnstyledButton-root" type="button" aria-label="Copy to clipboard"><span class="_root_tbbri_2" role="img" aria-hidden="true" style="visibility: visible; width: 0.75rem; height: 0.75rem;"><svg width="0.75rem" height="0.75rem" style="color: currentcolor; fill: currentcolor; display