e pull requests, review PRs, and manage issues\",\"keywords\":[\"github\",\"pull request\",\"PR\",\"push\",\"branch\",\"issue\",\"code review\",\"git\",\"clone\"],\"overview\":\"\\n## GitHub Workflow\\n\\nFor repositories hosted on GitHub:\\n\\n### Repository Setup\\n\\n- Use `github_repo_set_up` to clone repositories. It handles clone-if-not-present idempotently.\\n- Before cloning: check if the repo already exists via `ls`\\n- After cloning, check for steering files (`.kiro/steering/*.md`)\\n- When `&lt;repositories&gt;` tags are in the system prompt, those repositories MUST be cloned before any work.\\n\\n### Push and PR Workflow\\n\\n1. Always push to a new branch, never directly to main/master, unless explicitly asked\\n2. Use `github_push_to_remote` to push changes — never use `git push` directly via bash\\n3. Use `github_create_pull_request` to create the PR\\n4. PR title: concise, under 70 characters. Use the description for details.\\n5. PR description: summary of changes, what was tested, any blocked features\\n6. Before pushing, call `github_list_pull_requests` to check existing PRs for this session. If a PR exists and is merged or closed, create a new branch and open a new PR instead of reusing the old branch.\\n7. After completing work, always reference where the user can review it: include the PR link if one was created, or the branch URL (`https://github.com/{owner}/{repo}/tree/{branch}`) if only a branch was pushed.\\n\\n### Pre-flight Checks\\n\\n- Before pushing: run `git status` to verify changes are committed and you're on the correct branch\\n- Before creating a PR: verify the branch has been pushed\\n- Use `github_get_branch_name_from_pull_request` to get the branch name from an existing PR\\n\\n### CI Failure Recovery\\n\\nWhen a workflow run fails:\\n1. Use `github_list_failed_workflow_logs` to fetch the failure logs\\n2. Diagnose the root cause from the logs\\n3. Fix the issue\\n4. Push the fix and verify CI passes\\n\\n### Addressing PR Review Comments\\n\\nWhen asked to address PR review feedback:\\n1. Use `github_list_pr_comments` to retrieve review comments\\n2. Address each comment with a code change or explanation\\n3. Push fixes to the same branch (the PR updates automatically)\\n\\n### Issue Management\\n\\n- Use `github_get_issue` to fetch issue details when working on an issue\\n- Use `github_list_issues` to find related issues\\n- Use `github_list_issue_comments` to read discussion on an issue\\n\\n### Failure Handling\\n\\nPartial progress committed and pushed is always better than nothing.\\n- If the task is blocked, push whatever progress exists and create a draft PR\\n- Document blockers in the PR description\\n- Never silently fail — always surface what happened and why\\n\\n### Git Safety\\n\\n- Never run destructive git commands (force push, reset --hard, clean -f, branch -D) unless explicitly asked\\n- Never skip hooks (--no-verify) unless explicitly asked\\n- Never force push to main/master\\n- Never update git config\\n- Never use interactive git flags (-i)\\n\\n### Link Formatting\\n\\nFormat all GitHub URLs as markdown links:\\n- `[Pull Request #42](https://github.com/owner/repo/pull/42)`\\n- Never output bare URLs\\n\",\"steeringFiles\":[\"workflow.md\"],\"toolsByServer\":{\"github\":[{\"name\":\"clone_repository\",\"description\":\"Clone a GitHub repository to the workspace.\\n\\nWHEN TO USE:\\n- To get repository code before making changes\\n\\nNOTES:\\n- Authenticates automatically for private repos via provider gateway\\n- Max timeout: 840 seconds (14 min) - use shallow clone if it times out\",\"inputSchema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"owner\":{\"description\":\"Owner of github repository\",\"type\":\"string\"},\"repository_name\":{\"description\":\"Name of the repository\",\"type\":\"string\"},\"local_branch\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"string\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Local branch name to checkout\"},\"branch\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"string\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Remote branch to clone. If not specified, clones the default branch\"},\"clone_depth\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"integer\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Optional clone depth for shallow clone (e.g., 1 for latest commit only). github_repo_set_up defaults to depth=1 if not specified. Use larger values when full history is needed (e.g., PR feedback)\"}},\"required\":[\"owner\",\"repository_name\"]}},{\"name\":\"repo_set_up\",\"description\":\"Set up a git repository in the workspace. Defaults to shallow clone (depth=1) for performance.\\n\\nWHEN TO USE:\\n- To set up repository code before making changes\\n\\nNOTES:\\n- Defaults to shallow clone (depth=1). Override with clone_depth parameter when full history is needed\\n- Supports cloning a specific remote branch via the branch parameter\\n- Authenticates automatically\\n- Max timeout: 840 seconds (14 min) - use shallow clone if it times out\",\"inputSchema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"owner\":{\"description\":\"Owner of github repository\",\"type\":\"string\"},\"repository_name\":{\"description\":\"Name of the repository\",\"type\":\"string\"},\"local_branch\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"string\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Local branch name to checkout\"},\"branch\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"string\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Remote branch to clone. If not specified, clones the default branch\"},\"clone_depth\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"integer\"},{\"type\":\"null\"}],\"default\":null,\"description\":\"Optional clone depth for shallow clone (e.g., 1 for latest commit only). github_repo_set_up defaults to depth=1 if not specified. Use larger values when full history is needed (e.g., PR feedback)\"}},\"required\":[\"owner\",\"repository_name\"]}},{\"name\":\"push_to_remote\",\"description\":\"Push local branch to GitHub remote. ALWAYS use this tool instead of gi